description:
Anton Caravana was a renowned artist and illustrator in the Philippines working for Filipino comics companies. He came to the attention of Nestor Redondo who invited him to join an all Filipino "studio" which created work for comic companies in the United States. It was at this time that he began working for Warren Publishing.

His career was cut short in April 1981 when he was killed in an accident in his native Philippines.
name: Anton Caravana

deck: Blair Smith is a professional colorist currently working full time for the Living Corpse for Dynamite Comics.
description:
Blair Smith is a professional colorist currently working full time for the Living Corpse for Dynamite Comics. Blair is the newest colorist on the Living Corpse. His first issue Haunted, has received good reviews. He appears in an issue of Image Comics '68 as a colorist for a Pin up of Jungle Jim with Buz Hasson.

Colorist for the variant Cover for Army of Darkness vs Hack/Slash #5 cute subscription variant done by the whole The Living Corpse crew Ken Haeser, Buz Hasson & Blair Smith

He is also doing colors for an Indy Comic titled "Cronus" by comic author, Scott Beach. The first issue from Scott Beach's Superbrawl Series, Cronus vs the Black Cloud and the second issue Valiant vs Ripper.

Blair also colored for Hound Comics on Brimstone and The Borderhounds issue 8, as well as colors for Hounds Critical M.A.S.S.

In 2009 Blair worked on Michael San Giacomo's award winning “TALES OF THE STARLIGHT DRIVE-IN” from Image Comics, which won for the 2009 Comics Buyer’s Guide Annual Fan Awards!
name: Blair Smith

deck: An up and coming teenage actress, most famously known for playing Hit-Girl.
description:
Comic Related Roles

Hit-Girl

Moretz plays Hit-Girl, the foul-mouthed, ass kicking sidekick to Nic Cage's Big Daddy in Kick-Ass, a film based on the comic book series by Mark Millar and John Romita Jr. The movie was directed by Matthew Vaughn, who later went on to direct X-Men: First Class.

Moretz reprised her role in Kick-Ass 2.

Emily the Strange

Since 2010, Moretz has been chosen to be Emily the Strange, a Scientist, a Skater, and a girl with four cats.
name: Chloë Grace Moretz
